news.title: Smartworks leases 2.3 lakh sq ft space in Bengaluru
news.para: Smartworks currently has a growing footprint of approx. 7 Mn sq. ft. with a presence in 10 cities and 37 centres. caters to over 450 organisations across Forbes 2000 companies, MNCs, and unicorns.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's net profit rises 47% to Rs 2,613.75 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: As per the company, UltraTech Cement has now become a Rs 50,000 crore turnover company and the first Indian cement company to achieve this milestone.

news.title: Concrete jungles sprout as rules eased in Tamil Nadu
news.para: According to the old norms, if plot size (within Directorate of Town and Country Planning limits) exceeded 2,500 square metres, 10% of land should be handed over to local bodies through a gift deed.

news.title: Telangana: SCDRC jails builder for cheating flat buyers
news.para: The commission bench, comprising president Justice MSK Jaiswal, members Meena Ramanathan and K Ranga Rao, pronounced this order after hearing an execution plea filed by Dr R Renuka, her daughter, and son, who were aggrieved with the loss of money invested by her late husband R Eswari Prasad for buying a flat with Gharonda Builders and Developers.

news.title: After HC order, Chandigarh housing board gives seven days to remove violations
news.para: A senior CHB official said four structures were demolished on Wednesday and two on Thursday. UT director public relations (DPR) Rajiv Tewari was duty magistrate for the demolition exercise, he said.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government will increase supply of Valimai cement: Official
news.para: Speaking to reporters on the sidelines of the event, Tancem general manager Narmatha Devi said the government was increasing the supply of Valimai cement in the open market, since the price of private cement brands were rising.

news.title: Property tax defaulters in Panvel get Bombay HC relief
news.para: ​Separate writ petitions were filed by Kharghar Forum, the Kharghar Cooperative Housing Societies Federation and Kamothe Forum against the PCMC, seeking cancellation of property tax bills from October 2016 to financial year 2021-2022, and effecting it retrospectively.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board invites bidders of of IT Park on April 30
news.para: CHB’s chief executive officer (CEO) Yashpal Garg said they have invited prospective bidders. According to him, to make this auction a successful one, board officials will listen to prospective bidders before putting the plot in e-auction.

news.title: Indore development body gets approval to launch four schemes
news.para: IDA’s board-of-directors had in March this year announced its plan to take up as many as five new schemes to develop residential and commercial properties along with major roads costing around Rs 1,750 Crores.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board invites bids for 35 freehold properties till May 25
news.para: The six commercial properties (booths) are available in Sector 51A. Four have a reserve price of Rs 80 lakh each, while the remaining two are priced at Rs 85 lakh each.

news.title: Embassy REIT's CEO Michael Holland resigns; Vikaash Khdloya appointed as new CEO
news.para: ​Embassy REIT, sponsored by Embassy group and Blackstone, declared a distribution of Rs 499 crore or Rs 5.26 per unit for Q4 FY2022. With this, the cumulative distribution for FY2022 totals Rs 2,063 crore or Rs 21.76 per unit, 1 per cent higher than the initial guidance, of which 82 per cent is tax-free for unitholders.

news.title: Greater Noida: Two-day special camp for getting lease deeds done
news.para: Allottees who have been penalised for not getting the lease deed done within the stipulated time can also take advantage of the already announced one-time settlement scheme and register their property in this camp on the ground floor of the Authority’s office, officials said.

news.title: Gurugram: Increase in ground coverage for plots approved to curb building norm violations
news.para: With the increase in ground coverage, plot owners will be able to construct lifts, staircases and cut-outs without compromising the floor area ratio (FAR), which in turn, officials believe, will help bring down unauthorised construction in plotted areas.

news.title: Aaditya Thackeray suggests government, realtors should collaborate to build better cities
news.para: “We are shy about the peripheral tag of builder-politician that has been given to us. But I am here to say that whenever there is a builder-politician partnership which is positive, we have seen the good it can do to the citizens,” Thackeray said.

news.title: Maharashtra to re-allot stuck slum projects to new builders
news.para: ​There are 520 such stuck projects where the developer who had availed the original residents' consent for redevelopment but not delivered on the promises and also stopped paying rent given in transit, the state's housing minister Jitendra Awhad said.
